---
layout: base.njk
title: Gurl
---

<section class="hero">
    <h1>
        <span class="gradient-text">Gurl</span>
        <span class="subtitle">Free & Simple URL Shortener</span>
    </h1>
    <p>A free and <a href="https://github.com/oleeskild/gurl">open source</a> URL shortener. Easy to set up and deploy using free tools like GitHub and Vercel.</p>
    <a href="/quick-guide" class="button primary">Start with GitHub.dev <span class="icon">→</span></a>
    <a href="https://github.com/oleeskild/gurl#deploy-your-own" class="button">Deploy your own <span class="icon">↗</span></a>
</section>

<div class="fun-hero">
    <h2>URL Management, Simplified</h2>
    <p>Create memorable, shareable URLs for your team or organization. Perfect for internal resources, documentation, and frequently accessed links.</p>
</div>

<section id="shortcuts">
    <h2>All Shortcuts</h2>
    <div class="shortcut-grid">
        {%- set redirects = collections.redirectPages -%}
        {%- for redirect in redirects | slice(0, 4) -%}
            <article class="shortcut-card" style="--animation-order: {{ loop.index }};">
                {% set iconMap = {
                    "books": "📚",
                    "articles": "📄",
                    "demo": "🔍",
                    "pages": "📑"
                } %}
                {% set segment = redirect.url | getFirstUrlSegment %}
                {% set icon = iconMap[segment] if iconMap[segment] else 
                    "✨" %}

                <h3>{{ icon }}
                    {{ redirect.data.title }}</h3>
                <p>
                    {% if redirect.data.description %}
                        {{ redirect.data.description }}
                    {% else %}
                        Shortcut to {{ redirect.data.redirect_url }}.
                    {% endif %}
                </p>
                <footer>
                    <a href="{{ redirect.url }}">{{ redirect.url }}</a>
                </footer>
            </article>
        {%- endfor -%}
    </div>
</section>

<section id="how-to" class="how-to-section">
    <h2>How To Create a New Shortcut</h2>

    <ol class="step-list">
        <li style="--item-index: 1">Create a new markdown file in the <code>src</code> directory</li>
        <li style="--item-index: 2">The file path will become the URL (e.g., <code>src/books/mybook.md</code> creates <code>/books/mybook</code>)</li>
        <li style="--item-index: 3">Add frontmatter to configure the redirect</li>
    </ol>

    <details class="code-example">
        <summary>Show example code</summary>
        <pre><code>---
# All of these have defaults:
layout: redirect.njk  <!-- Default from markdown.js -->
title: Your Page Title  <!-- Default: Uses redirect_url -->
redirect_url: https://destination-url.com  <!-- Default: https://example.com -->
redirect_delay: 5000  <!-- Default: 3000 milliseconds (3 seconds) -->
---

Optional content to display on the redirect page</code></pre>
    </details>

</section>

